{
  "stem": "14810.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But at 8:00, he came and he checked it, and he said I will need operate, to be operated on.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They took me in Friday.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They operated on me.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I remember even now, when they woke me up after the operation, the doctor showed me the splinter was about that-- he said, you're a fortunate man.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "He said another split hair would have-- would have severed my main artery.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I-- I would have been killed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But my troubles had just started.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I remember I was there for two months.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I know a lot of people couldn't believe it at Auschwitz, because they don't-- in Auschwitz, if you were sick or some severe, they didn't bother.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "They took you away to the crematorium.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What fortunate for me-- you see, the Red Cross used to come in every few months for its check and inspection.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I remember they wanted to show it to the Red Cross.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember when the Red Cross came from Switzerland, and these SS men-- I was in-- on the bunk laying, and the SS men came up to me with this Red Cross man, and they asked me, how old are you?",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I said 19.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I remember he said to the-- to the man, you see, the Americans almost killed him, and we just cured him and-- and brought him back to life.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was-- everything was for propaganda.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Maybe that's the reason they kept me there and they treated me, because the treatment was terrible.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I got pains and had no painkillers.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was terrible.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The pains were unbearable.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I lost so much weight there because I couldn't eat my-- for my-- I don't know how-- how I survived that thing.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember that was already October, November '44.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
